The paper discusses the limitations of traditional information retrieval models and proposes a semantic information retrieval model for Arabic language. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA) and Latent Semantic Index (LSI), which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML) fields. This indicates that the paper may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-categories.
